Vyatta config validator is a script that validates Vyatta config.boot file.
If config.boot is valid, script exits silently and returns zero.
If config.boot is invalid, script warns user about spotted errors and returns non-zero value,
which equals to spotted error count.
When launched without parameters, script validates /opt/vyatta/etc/config/config.boot,
or takes alternative config.boot path as only allowed parameter.
